This paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for sensitive applications, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper specifically focuses on the LIME algorithm, which is used for interpretability of machine learning models, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of LIME for image classification tasks, as mentioned in the abstract, suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) could also be a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential limitations of LIME, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
